            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 2,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1572603378,
            "creation_date": 1572603378,
            "body": "<p>I think you have to add the location to your static folder in the application.properties <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>spring.resources.static-locations=file:&lt;location&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>And also to access the file don't give the <code>static-locations<\/code> folder name. you can access it directly if it is not in a subfolder. like this<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://localhost:8080/filename.ext\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">http://localhost:8080/filename.ext<\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 58657482,
            "question_id": 58447927
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AAuE7mBQ0Lsz6nLWzXyqVAQwpUP_dah-4IeNti2cwYuw1w=k-s256",
                "account_id": 16920758,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 12237635,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/12237635/melan-pangan",
                "reputation": 1,
                "display_name": "Melan Pangan"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1571391627,
            "creation_date": 1571391627,
            "body": "<p>You cannot access your file if it's not on your static folder location, otherwise you need to specify the exact path and file name to access it.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 58448113,
            "question_id": 58447927
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/paTG6.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 9168614,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 6817140,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6817140/mohit-dodhia",
