            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1571403217,
            "creation_date": 1571403217,
            "body": "<p>So I have been making a file sharing web app using Spring Boot and here is how I have facilitated getting files from the database. I will focus specifically on your problem because it is very similar to what I faced a few days ago.<\/p>\n\n<p>Firstly, I make a POJO class <code>Files<\/code> which has details like <code>filename<\/code>, <code>lastmodified<\/code>, and some others which are not relevant to your problem here.<\/p>\n\n<p>I get the files from the database using a DAO class, add the above mentioned attributes in an ArrayList and return the ArrayList back to the Controller class. In the Controller class, using <code>request<\/code> object I do the following: <code>request.setAttribute(\"files\", files);<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p>Now in my jsp file, I use JSTL to get files like this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;c:forEach var=\"j\" items=\"${files}\"&gt;\n    &lt;td&gt;\n        &lt;a href=\"resources/files/${j.getFilename()}\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"&gt;${j.getFile()}&lt;/a&gt;\n    &lt;/td&gt;\n&lt;/c:forEach&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><code>resources/files/<\/code> is the path where my files are stored after being uploaded and using <code>target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"<\/code> enables me to open files (files which the browser allows to be opened such as pdf and text files) in a new tab and those which cannot be opened get automatically downloaded. <\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 58451359,
            "question_id": 58447927
        }
    ],
